<title type="html"><![CDATA[Why is Brazil &quot;PAL&quot;?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3511&amp;p=26104#p26104"><![CDATA[
This works because 1. SECAM has the same timings as PAL 50 Hz, and 2. consumer video components in Europe use SCART, an RGB interconnect. Once the signals are decoded to components, they both end up as analog video with a 15.6 kHz horizontal scan frequency and 50 Hz vertical scan frequency.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Aug 02, 2007 9:29 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
