<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3511&amp;p=26099#p26099"><![CDATA[
Which only means that "an NTSC video game" and "a PAL video game" have always been misnomers for "a 240p/480i video game" and "a 288p/576i video game", except in the case of early consoles such as the Atari 2600 that used significantly different palettes for the two color systems.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Aug 02, 2007 4:23 am</p><hr />
